description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated individual to join the Medical Imaging Department of the Royal Devon &amp; Exeter Hospital as Bookings Clerk/Receptionist on a full time basis (37.5hrs per week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Appointment Clerk/Receptionist you will play an important part in the service our Department provides to our patients, ensuring that they receive appointments in a timely manner. You will need to be able to thrive in a busy and fast paced environment. We are looking for someone who is a really good communicator, keeps calm under pressure, is caring and motivated by helping others and working in a team. Attention to detail is a prerequisite for anyone considering this post, as is computer literacy. Helping our patients as a Appointment Clerk/Receptionist involves taking their calls and helping them to book the right appointment, answering their general questions and positively making your mark as an important part of the overall service our Department provides.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate needs to be self motivated, highly organised, empathetic, calm, flexible and hard working with excellent communication and IT skills. A knowledge of hospital systems would be preferable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Imaging Department is one of the largest and busiest departments in the RD&amp;E Hospital. In this department we see patients from GP surgeries, hospital clinics, in patient wards, the Accident &amp; Emergency Department and from hospitals across the UK. The department is open for out patient appointments 8am – 8pm, 7 days a week, as well as providing 24 hour on site cover for urgent cases referred from within the hospital and the Accident &amp; Emergency Department. Medical Imaging consists of a wide range of modalities including General Radiography, CT, MRI, Ultrasound, Fluoroscopy and Interventional Radiology and in any 24 hour period approximately 500 patients receive diagnostic examinations or treatment in the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you require any further information, please contact Val Ramsay, Administration Team Leader, Radiology Department on 01392 408554.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
